tent and context. It positions the Firework Books at a crucial stage in the development of gunpowder artillery, offering an unparalleled insight into fifteenth-century gunpowder technology at a critical juncture of military and technological change at the end of the Middle Ages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGunpowder industryzGermany. 0aGunpowderxHistory. 4aBibliography & Manuscripts. 4aMedieval History. 4aMilitary History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aBellifortis.  aBüchsenmeister.  aFeuerwerkbuch.  aNew High German.  aartillery.  amanuscript studies.  atechnology.  awarfare.  aweapons manufacture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311143096640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781805431756?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781805431756423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781805431756/original  a978-3-11-143096-6  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles